article.headline: Harvard 37, Princeton 3
article.story: BOSTON -- Collier Winters threw two touchdowns and ran for another to lead Harvard in a 37-3 rout of Princeton on Saturday. Winters was 13-for-19 with 190 yards and two interceptions, and also rushed for 26 yards for the Crimson (4-2, 3-0 Ivy League). A 77-yard touchdown connection between Winters and Chris Lorditch on the reciever's only catch of the day put Harvard ahead 7-0 less than 3 minutes into the opening quarter. Ben Bologna kicked a 19-yard field goal to pull the Tigers (1-5, 0-3) within 7-3, but that would be the last time Princeton would score. Winters threw a 3-yard touchdown to Kyle Juszczyk and ran for a 3-yard score to help put Harvard ahead 24-3 at the half. Gino Gordon's 3-yard rushing TD and Cheng Ho's 2-yarder sealed the scoring in the second half. Harvard had two turnovers to just one for Princeton, but the Crimson outgained the Tigers 457-157.
